text: Waseda Jitsugyo (The formal Japanese description is 早稲田大学系属早稲田実業学校) is a Japanese private school with an elementary school (), junior and senior high school (). Waseda Jitsugyo was founded in 1901, in Tokyo and attached to Waseda University. This means that all students who have successfully finished this school are allowed to enter Waseda University. == Notes == == Other websites == * Waseda Jitsugyo Category:1900s establishments in Japan Category:1901 establishments Category:High schools in Japan Category:Waseda University
